Il Divo;;80;;92;;NC;;Writer-director Paolo Sorrentino received the Cannes Jury Prize for his biopic of the fabled Italian politician Giulio Andreotti (Toni Servillo). The film covers a large portion of Andreotti's seven terms as prime minister of Italy, and concerns itself with the inner machinations of the man known as "Beelzebub," the intrigue surrounding the disappearance of his political enemies (including two-time prime minister Aldo Moro), and the role of the Mafia in postwar Italy.;;Drama,Biography,History;;Paolo Sorrentino;;2009;;Toni Servillo,Anna Bonaiuto,Piera Degli Esposti,Paolo Graziosi,Giulio Bosetti,Flavio Bucci,Carlo Buccirosso,Giorgio Colangeli,Alberto Cracco,Lorenzo Gioielli,Gianfelice Imparato;;https://www.rottentomatoes.com/m/il_divo